HEADWORD: Prænomen
<hw>Pr⟦ae⟧*no"men</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pr⟦ae⟧nomina</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>nomen</ets> name.]</ety> <fld>(Rom.
Antiq.)</fld> <def>The first name of a person, by which individuals of
the same family were distinguished, answering to our <xex>Christian
name</xex>, as Caius, Lucius, Marcus, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Praenominical</ent>⟦br⟧
